(secondQuint)Immunogenicity and Safety Study of GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) Biologicals' Combined Measles-mumps-rubella (MMR) Vaccine in Subjects Four to Six Years of Age.

 The GSK Biologicals' MMR vaccine (Priorix(R)) and Merck's MMR vaccine (M-M-R(R)II) are referred to as Inv_MMR vaccine and Com_MMR vaccine respectively.

 2 lots of the comparator vaccine (Com_MMR_L1 and Com_MMR_L2) will be used, but the 2 lots will be analysed as a pool.

 The Inv_MMR vaccine will be administered as a second dose to children who already received a first dose Com_MMR vaccine.

 Since the second dose of a MMR vaccine in the US is routinely co-administered with DTaP-IPV vaccine (Kinrix(R)) and varicella vaccine (VV) (ProQuad(R) or Varivax(R)), some children will receive one dose of these vaccines along with either of the MMR vaccines.

